<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id1225551f-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s1118"><num value="1118">§ 1118.</num><heading> Documents beyond scope of ordinary departmental business</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A book or document not having to do with the ordinary business transactions of the executive departments may not be printed on the requisition of a department unless expressly authorized by Congress.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id12255520-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1264">82 Stat. 1264</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id12255521-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id12255522-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on 44 U.S. Code, 1964 ed., § 219a (<ref href="/us/act/1905-03-03/ch1484/s1">Mar. 3, 1905, ch. 1484, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/33/1249">33 Stat. 1249</ref>).</p>
</note>
</notes>
